 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">✅ Keeping Yourself And The Workout Station Clean</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764626941" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764626941" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Wiping yourself and the exercise equipment before, during, and after a workout is important.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">If you work out at home, having a clean workout station the next time you want to exercise can affect your mood and motivation.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">If you’re using a public gym or sharing your home equipment, the next person using the equipment will be thankful and, hopefully, reciprocate.</span></p><p>This keeps the gym more hygienic and safer.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Sweat itself is not known to carry diseases, but it can be a source of moisture that can create an environment for bacteria to grow.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">However, sweat is not the only bodily fluid we leave behind on workout machines, as </span>exhaling can leave behind respiratory droplets which can transfer Covid-19 and similarly transmitted diseases.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506608137" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670506608137"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">✅ Workout Towels Are A Convenient Hygienic Solution</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781540256" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781540256" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Workout towels are compact and easy to carry, making them a convenient accessory for outdoor activities or trips to the gym.</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">By removing sweat, dirt, and other particles through wiping, they help you keep your preemptive hygiene up before you get to do a change of clothes, wash your face, shower, etc.</span><br></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569822" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670485569822"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">✅ Wiping Your Face From Sweat Keeps The Skin Clear</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569821" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569821" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>As you exercise, <a href="https://www.aad.org/public/diseases/acne/causes/workouts" class="" target="_blank">apart from sweating, you build up oil, dirt, and other bacteria on your skin, which can lead to skin imperfections such as acne.</a></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">To prevent this, proper hygiene is necessary before, during, and after workouts.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">This means wiping your skin from sweat using clean gym sweat towels and, when necessary, rinsing your face.</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781715573" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675781715573" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/7b58dcc0-01c5-4150-ad49-ebd5ca00da07/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/workout-towel.jpg" alt="workout-towel" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506766447" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670506766447"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">When Do You Need A Workout Towel?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569819" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569819" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The short answer to when you need to have a gym towel for sweat removal is - always.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">There are no drawbacks to having one on you at all times as you exercise.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Even if you’re not actively using it for your workout, you can just keep it by your side until you eventually need it.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Many public gyms have workout towels as part of mandatory equipment, apart from the usual clean shoes and clothing.</span></p><p>Some gyms won’t allow you to check in and rent a locker unless you show a clean towel on entry and, if you don’t bring your own, they’ll require you to rent one at the counter.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Many gyms already had this requirement for years, but those that didn’t slowly add it as part o Covid-19 safety protocols.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">As for when you actually need to use it, it will depend on how much you’re sweating and whether you’re the only person occupying the equipment.</span></p><p>For example, wiping your palms and equipment handles between sets is always a good idea, as it will prevent you from losing your grip and potentially hurting yourself.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Once you’re done using a machine or barbell, wipe it to leave the workout station hygienic for the next person (or yourself when you come back, in the case of home gyms).<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Placing a towel over the surface area where your body will touch the exercise equipment, such as a back or chest pad, can prevent you from having to clean it later.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Exercise towels are a must-have for cardio machines, as the nature of their exercise will have you sweating a lot more.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Wiping yourself will not only keep the machine clean, but sweat marks can leave slippery spots on things like treadmills and ellipticals, which can cause a slip.</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675931380249" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675931380249" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/851ccab8-a8bb-4c36-9228-be5e076b8f9d/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/towel.jpg" alt="towel" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" width="1200" height="800" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675846312914" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675846312914"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What To Look For In Workout Towels?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081935903" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081935903"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Material Quality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081937983" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081937983" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Material quality is arguably the most important characteristic to look for in gym sweat towels.<br><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">Overall, the quality of the towel will correlate with its absorbency, durability, comfort, hygiene factor, and even looks.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">A low quality towel will not only fail to keep the liquid in, it will tear more easily and lose softness faster.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">It can also release its color which can stain your workout clothes or equipment, but also release toxic chemicals.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">The best workout towels are made from soft cotton, microfiber, velour, or other premium materials.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Towels made from higher quality materials can withstand repeated use and washing without losing their shape, texture, or softness.<br></span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">This also helps them keep the premium aesthetic over longer periods of time, which can lead to fewer replacements and spending less cash outlay.</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705419289810" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705419289810" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705419289799" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705419289799" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705419289735" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1705419289735"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705419289815" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1705419289815" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" 