t" id="e-1705419289790" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1705419289790"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1705419289693" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1705419289693"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781843365" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781843365"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Absorbency</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764772057" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764772057" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Absorbency of fitness towels refers to their ability to take in and hold (absorb) liquids.<div>You’ll mostly be using your gym towel for sweat removal, either from yourself or from the workout equipment.</div><div>Occasionally, you might have to deal with a drink spill and, in the case of plain water, you might even use the same towel for it.</div><div>If your gym sweat towels don’t hold in the liquid, feel wet to the touch, or even drip, then you need to get more absorbent ones.</div><div><br></div><div>The absorbency rating is usually directly tied to material quality, as better material tends to have better absorption.</div><div>For example, <a href="https://wspehsu.ucsf.edu/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/FactSheet_Microfiber.pdf" class="" target="_blank">a microfiber towel can absorb as much as seven times its weight in liquid and covers the same surface area as a cotton cloth as much as four times larger.</a></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781867139" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781867139"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Softness</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781867996" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781867996" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Softness as a characteristic of fitness towels is often subjective.<div>Some people prefer very soft microfiber gym towels because of their comfort or in case they have sensitive skin.</div><div><br></div><div>However, some people prefer using a more rugged, textured surface, especially on their face, to get the exfoliated skin feeling after a workout.</div><div>Softness is especially preferable if you wipe yourself from sweat a lot during workouts, such as when performing cardio exercises.</div><div>Repeated wiping with a rough surface towel can easily lead to redness or even minor scratches.</div></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787081135" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675787081135" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/ed3d204a-7607-4819-8523-4b98f0fe224e/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/sweat-towel.jpg" alt="best workout towel" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787155402" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787155402"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Price VS Quality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787156027" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787156027" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675847238651" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675847238651"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>At the end of the day, sweat towels for gym and home exercising are dispensable and, unless you go for a huge name brand, inexpensive.</p><p>For the average person, you don’t want to overspend on towels because they tend to get lost, torn, and worn out over time.</p><p>I always recommend getting multiple athletic towels to have spares.</p><p><br></p><p>This way, you won’t have to worry about your towel not being clean, in case you don’t find time to wash it between workouts.</p><p>The goal of these lists is to help you best spend your hard-earned money.</p><p>Even though some items have higher ratings than others, it doesn’t mean they’re necessarily worse.</p><p>Depending on your budget and preferences, one product may be more suited for you than another.</p><p><br></p><p>That’s why I always list multiple products and explain their pros and cons.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787198507" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787198507" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787440275" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787440275"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787464047" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787464047"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are Gym Towels Worth It?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787599490" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787599490" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>High-quality athletic towels will improve your workout experience. Wiping yourself and your equipment clean after each use is hygienic and will save you cleaning time later.</div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787889767" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787889767"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do Microfiber Towels Absorb Sweat?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787891143" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787891143" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Yes, microfiber gym towels significantly outperform towels made from other common materials such as cotton.&nbsp;</div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787928690" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787928690"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I Wash My Gym Towel After Every Use?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787929995" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787929995" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Typically, you should wash exercise towels after every use, especially if you use a public gym.<div>However, exceptions can be made with high-quality absorbing towels if you’ve barely used them during a home workout session.</div><div>Then you can get away with washing it after every two or three workouts, although rinsing to refresh it after use is still recommended for hygienic reasons.</div><div><br></div></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1675788016791" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1675788016791" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org","@type": "FAQPage","mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question","name": "Are Gym Towels Worth It?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "High-quality athletic towels will improve your workout experience. Wiping yourself and your equipment clean after each use is hygienic and will save you cleaning time later."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Do Microfiber Towels Absorb Sweat?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Yes, microfiber gym towels significantly outperform towels made from other common materials such as cotton."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Should I Wash My Gym Towel After Every Use?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Typically, you should wash exercise towels after every use, especially if you use a public gym. However, exceptions can be made with high-quality absorbing towels if you’ve barely used them during a home workout session. Then you can get away with washing it after every two or three workouts, although rinsing to refresh it after use is still recommended for hygienic reasons."}}]}</script></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1675801378551" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpi